---

The error is a standard Git “unmerged files” failure because `git commit` was run while there are still unresolved merge conflicts. The log shows dozens of `offline-folder-rag/.../__pycache__/*.pyc` files marked as `U` (unmerged), so Git refused to create the commit until those conflicts are resolved and the files are staged (or removed if they shouldn’t be tracked).

_**Agent (model gpt-5.1-codex-mini, mode Agent)**_

<think><details><summary>Thought Process</summary>
**Suggesting commands to fix unmerged files**</details></think>

---

Run `git status` to verify the unmerged pyc files, then resolve or remove them and stage the result. A quick way to drop those merged conflicts (since `.pyc` files should be ignored) is:

```bash
git rm --cached offline-folder-rag/**/*.pyc
git commit
```

If you’re in the middle of a merge and want to back out entirely:

```bash
git merge --abort
```

Either command set clears the conflict so you can proceed.
